{{doomwiki}}
'''Vanilla Doom''' is used to refer to [[Doom]] running without a [[source port]] on the original executable. In order to avoid desynchronizations in [[multiplayer]], players must have their vanilla Doom's [[IWAD]] [[IWAD Patching|patched]] to 1.9. Rebuilding the [[NODES]] in the original maps will also cause them to desynchronize. Foreign language versions of the vanilla Doom [[IWAD]]s may have rebuilt versions of the nodes as well, making them incompatible with one another in multiplayer.
